Description:
[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Possibilities: 1) Landscape by Bruegel, figures by C. M. (cf. the drawing of the same subject by C.M.); 2) Landscape by Bruegel, figures by Jan Massys; 3) Landscape by C.M., figures by Jan M.; 4) The whole by Gillis Mostaert: but why then the Massys signature? It can not be read as G.M., as it it runs CMA. 1557 would be possible for all three; 5) Landscape by Herri met de Bles and figures by C.M. - but this is unlikely as Bles was the other artist and the landscpaes dominates;
[blad 2, recto] : Dr. Becker Landscape [sic]: 6) Roger H. Marijnissen, Bruegel, Brussels 1969, p. 80, cat. N° 1; 5) [sic] Piero BIANCONI, L'opera completa di Bruegel (Classici dell'Arte), Milan, Rizzoli, 1967, p. 88, catal. N° 5 as 'new attribution' without opinion; 4) [sic] Tolnay, Burl.Mag. 1965 The Towneley Lectionarium also repr. in Bianconi, p. 84.; 1) [sic] (Fischer) Sale Luzern, Nov. 1724, N° 2642, Cornelis Massys Monogrammist C.M.A. (15)57; 2) [sic] Grossmann, I, 1956; 3) Zürich, Unbekannte ?heit; 4) Zwollo, Corn. Massys, Nederl. Kunsthist.Jaarboek, XVI, 1965, p. 64, Abb. 20; 5) Tolnay 1965 - Bruegel cf. Townely Lectionarium; 6) Grossmann II; 7) Bianconi 1967, Bruegel; 8) Faggin 1968, La Pittura ad Anversa nel Cinquecento, 1968, p. 82, n. 41; 9) Marijnissen 1969; 10) Brussels, Exh. Bruegel et son Monde, 1969, p. 43, cat. N° 1, accepted as Bruegel, also listed p. [sic] compared with engraved ship; [blad 2, verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. compare, apart from boats, for sky: Clovio miniature, as well as View of Naples.
